### 3. 🔴 No Global Error Handler
Unhandled errors will crash the process or leak stack traces to clients. Add a centralized error middleware:

```js
// Place this after all routes
app.use((err, req, res, next) => {
  console.error(err.stack); // log internally, never expose to client
  res.status(err.status || 500).json({ error: 'Internal server error' });
});
```

Also handle uncaught async failures at the process level:
```js
process.on('uncaughtException', (err) => {
  console.error('Uncaught exception:', err);
  process.exit(1);
});
process.on('unhandledRejection', (reason) => {
  console.error('Unhandled rejection:', reason);
  process.exit(1);
});
```

---

### 4. 🟠 No 404 Handler
Unknown routes silently fall through. Add a catch-all:

```js
app.use((req, res) => {
  res.status(404).json({ error: 'Not found' });
});
```

---

